⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Stan Lee
node MLR · MLR · ⟦Stan Lee:MLR:9e7413⟧

WHO   — Stan Lee — the comic-book sage
WHAT  — The sage cameo: real-world comics royalty dispensing a knowingly made-up parable, and inventing the modern movie-cameo in the process.
WHERE — MLR · Mallrats (1995)  Framework inputs: Mallrats (1995, dir. Kevin Smith, Gramercy/View Askew); verified cast & facts  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Brodie's gospel needs its prophet to appear in the flesh — and Stan Lee is the prophet.
HOW   — By telling Brodie a fabricated story of lost love (and, off-screen, insisting on an 'only kidding' beat to protect his real marriage).

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I let the great love of my life get away, true believer — well, no, I didn't, I'm only kidding. But the lesson lands anyway.

